On Tue, 17 Jul 2007 chrismusk(-at-)aim.com wrote:

> I need recommendations on how to lessen the?mechanical resistance to turning?over,

Remove the plugs and put a few drops of motor oil in each cylinder.  If it
does not spin freely then you either have a bad starter or the engine has
serious issues.  The fact that you find the engine hard to turn over
points to the engine.
